In a large heatproof bowl, combine chocolate, butter and vanilla. Set aside In a saucepan over medium heat, bring cream to a full rolling boil, without stirring. Once it starts to climb up sides of pan, remove from heat and pour over chocolate. Let stand for 2 minutes, undisturbed. Whisk mixture until chocolate has fully melted and ganache is smooth. Use immediately or cover and refrigerate for up to 7 days.